			<h1>Science!</h1>
			<br />

			<p>
				Welcome to OurVapes Science! We at OurVapes are committed to providing the latest scientifically defensible information about the health effects of vaping. This space is reserved for peer reviewed academic articles and information and data from government agencies. We do our best to stay current, but if you find something new and sciency, let us know.
			</p>
			<br />

			<strong>
				<a href = "http://ntr.oxfordjournals.org/content/16/1/108.full" class = "link">
					Pilot Investigation of Changes in Readiness and Confidence to Quit Smoking after E-cigarette Experimentation and 1 Week of Use
				</a>
				<p>
				Theodore L. Wagener, Ellen Meier, Jessica J. Hale, Elisha R. Oliver, Maggie L. Warner, Leslie M. Driskill, Stephen R. Gillaspy, Michael B. Siegel, Steven Foster
				</p>
			</strong>
			<p>
				This was a small study of 30 smokers who identified themselves as not interested in quitting. They were introduced to e-cigs and given a week's supply to take home. After using e-cigs for a week, they showed a higher readiness and confidence to quit. They also showed a reduction of their regular cigarette consumption.
			</p>
			<%= render "science_citation", id: "pilot" %>
			<br />
			<div id = "citation-pilot" class = "citation collapse out">
