			<strong>
			<a href = "http://www.biomedcentral.com/content/pdf/1940-0640-8-5.pdf" class = "link">
			Perceived efficacy of e-cigarettes versus nicotine replacement therapy among successful e-cigarette users: a qualitative approach
			</a>
			<p>
			Amanda M. Barbeau, Jennifer Burda, Michael Siegel
			</p>
			</strong>
			<p>
				Great article about how vapers feel about switching from cigs to vaping. The authors identify the things that make us love vaping - the bio-behavioral feedback (nerd speak for throat hit), social benefits of being in the vaping community, hobby elements (we do love our gear) and personal identity(have I mentioned that I am a vaper?).
			</p>
